headline.main: ADMIRAL MAHAN, NAVAL CRITIC, DIES; Overstudy of Strategic Problems of War Hastened His End at 74, Friends Say. GAINED FAME FROM BOOK "The Influence of Sea Power Upon History" Responsible for Present German Navy ;- Our Navy's Tribute. ADMIRAL MAHAN, NAVAL CRITIC, DIES

abstract: death, career, tribute from Navy Dept. and British press
snippet: WASHINGTON, D.C., Dec. 1. -- Rear Admiral Alfred Thayer Mahan, U.S.N., retired. America's foremost naval strategist and the world's greatest authority on sea power, died suddenly at the United States Naval Hospital here at 7:15 o'clock this mornin...

byline.original: Special to The New York Times
